-- Repeatable migration: seed the public activity database.
--
-- A fresh install has an empty activity picker without these — the add-activity
-- screen loads its dropdown from activity_database. They carry their real
-- production UUIDs, so this is idempotent against an existing database and
-- physical_activities.activity_id keeps pointing at the same rows everywhere.
--
-- ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING, deliberately: this seed will never overwrite a row
-- that already exists. Correcting a MET value on a live database is a
-- versioned migration, not an edit here.
--
-- The 449k BLS/FDC food rows are NOT seeded here — those are loaded by
-- tmp/import_bls_to_postgres.py / import_fdc_to_postgres.py.

